news.title: Construction equipment sales to breach the 2018 peak next year
news.para: “We expect to see a growth of roughly 10% this year, on the total market side. The growth is largely driven from segments like coal mining and handling,” Dimitrov Krishnan, Head, Volvo Construction Equipment said.

news.title: Fix public notices on Vasai-Virar buildings facing demolition orders: Bombay HC to VVMC
news.para: ​However, it sought demolition statistics for 2 years after petitioners' advocate Ajay Jaiswal said VVMC is not following a 2018 government resolution that directed planning authorities/corporations to file caveats before a civil court after passing demolition orders so that they will be heard.

news.title: Bengaluru: Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout allottees seek relief from BDA penalisation
news.para: As per the sale deed between the BDA and allottees, the latter have to construct houses within five years of allotment. The BDA can impose a penalty on those who fail to construct houses within five years of site allotment. As per the agreement, around 5,000 allottees have to pay the penalty for keeping the sites vacant for more than five years.

news.title: Delhi: Special campaign to focus on registration of construction sites
news.para: Rai said DPCC will take action against those project proponents who have not registered their construction and demolition sites on the C&D portal for self-assessment of dust control norms.

news.title: Gurugram: Around 200 Mahira Buildtech buyers protest, demand possession
news.para: The department had recently cancelled the licence of the project in Sector 68 for irregularities, including the submission of forged and fabricated bank documents.

news.title: Ranveer Singh buys Rs 119-crore luxury quadruplex in Mumbai's Bandra
news.para: The apartment, which is spread across the 16th, 17th, 18th and 19th floor of the tower, has a total 11,266 sq ft of carpet area and a 1,300 sq ft exclusive terrace. The deal is valued at over 1 lakh per sq ft, in line with the ongoing property rates in the vicinity.

news.title: Centre asks Delhi government to make NOC mandatory for L&DO property registration
news.para: According to the letter written by the L&DO, a department under the housing and urban affairs ministry, there are around 57,389 residential, 1,597 commercial, 1,430 institutional and 110 industrial units under the jurisdiction of the department in Delhi.

news.title: Chandigarh: Estate office holds grievance redressal camp
news.para: In addition, applications related to various services including occupancy certificate, building plans, updations and no dues certificates.

news.title: Mumbai: Kurla housing society held guilty of not dealing with leak in apartment
news.para: ​The owners of the leaking flat, Shahabuddin and Nasareen Ahmed have been directed to pay a compensation of Rs65,000 to the 75-year-old complainant Anwarali Meharali, who said that his flat was severely damaged due to the leakage.

news.title: Bengaluru: Utopia Lakeview Layout residents impacted by waterlogging
news.para: Waterlogging in layout began after Tharabanahalli Lake was rejuvenated under a CSR initiative

news.title: Bengaluru: Malleswaram residents not keen on highrises
news.para: In their project, which spanned 8-10 weeks, the students found that most of the residential apartments are only two- or three-storeyed.

news.title: Experts moot changes in Bengaluru civic body's draft building bylaws
news.para: Six professional bodies from various fields such as geotechnicality, construction and civil engineering have made several recommendations to change or alter some rules proposed in Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike's draft of building bylaws.

news.title: Think twice before you apply to Ahmedabad urban development body online
news.para: According to AUDA's annual report for 2021-22, it received 398 online applications for approval of development plans for buildings with a maximum height of 15m. AUDA approved 206 plans and cancelled 180 applications.

news.title: Residents of dilapidated building in Mumbai to be forcibly evicted, says BMC
news.para: Recently 19 people lost their lives after a dilapidated structure crashed in Kurla. The BMC willl issue a fresh notice to all residents living in these structures.

news.title: MHADA to undertake digital mapping, survey of its land parcels across Maharashtra
news.para: The housing board has already started the work and is currently in advanced stages of developing the Geographical Information System (GIS) driven mapping and Robotic Process Automation (RAP) systems for the same.
